<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1152">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 81.2.00/9952.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                                        Juárez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso, Texas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-23">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>No reliable news from Chihuahua City, but the general impression is
                                that it will fall into the hands of the rebels without battle.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>